      VALUES ("The Batrider is best at ganking. He has awesome ulti that disables and drags the targeted unit for 3.0/3.5/4.0 seconds, which is very good for bringing the targeted hero next to your allies or your tower. Batrider is hardly killable, as he has a stacking slow and a skill that makes him a flying unit, therefore he can walk through trees and cliffs. ", "At early game lasthit as much as you can. Rush Urn + PT + Perseverance. Spam Sticky Napalm, stack 4-5 times and then cast Firefly, cast Urn on the weakest enemy and rush your enemies. If you are careful enough you will kill the heroes you lane against. Use Flamebreak to ensure at least 1 kill. Gank other lanes if needed.", "Start to roam. You already have Force Staff - Gank as much as possible. When ganking cast Sticky Napalm 2-3 times, cast Urn, cast Firefly, cast ult and push yourself with Force Staff closer to your allies. If it's possible - upgrade your PT to BoT. Tp each time a big wave is available. Stack 4 times Sticky Napalm and then Flamebreak.", "This is the period of the game where you are not that useful. Try to push a lane and finish the game. Build BKB and bravely go next to a enemy hero and lasso it, bring him next to your allies and kill him. When teamfight happens - spam Sticky Napalm and rush through the battlefield with Firefly.", "The orange miniguide", "playdota", "http://www.playdota.com/guides/the-orange-miniguide-to-batrider", "Batrider", "40");
