      VALUES ("Mangix has a high base damage to begin with, which makes last hitting quite easy. His attack animation is quite fast compared to other melee heroes and he has a good cast animation as well. He has average MS and enough armor to compensate for the laning phase harasses, a high starting STR and STR gain which makes him beefier compared to other STR heroes. Though he has good points, his lack of INT and AGI make his early and late game potential quite horrid, thus making him a good mid game carry who can semi- carry late game.", "Your goal during early game is fairly simple; build your core, and survive (which shouldn't be much of a problem to you). By the end of early game, you should have these items: Power Treads, Ring of Basilius, Ring of Protection, Magic Wand", "When mid game comes, this is where you truly shine. This is when you complete your Aghanims and start raping those heroes 3 is to 1. The peak of your strength is when you get your Aghanims so be sure to abuse it while you can. This would also be a good time to try to win the game with the help of your teammates. Your main goal is to get your Aghanims, and do your best to push at least the first two towers of each lane (or completely Mega one lane to keep the pressure). Remember, your Panda's have amazing strength once they have Aghanims. Use it to push, kill, and survive using whatever means necessary. Aghanims increases your Panda's strength by A LOT. Vlad's provides an aura to make them beefier, and the lifesteal is good too.", "Late game is where you start losing potential. If those hard carries haven't gotten MKB yet then your lucky that you shut them down from early on. If they do on the other hand, then once you Split, cast Cyclone on them and take out the supports instead. Don't expect people to still fear you at this point. They can survive your combo during this stage, and most of them have items to escape you (Force Staff, Lothars, etc.). Start building your AC. This item will support your Panda's and at the same time turn you into a tank- ish carry. This item is the best for Panda as it gives a smooth transition from semi- carry to tank- carry. It has good synergy with Vlad's too. AC provides armor for your Panda's, a minus armor aura for the enemies you attack, and an increase in AS which helps your Panda's in every way. This time, don't use Split right away after Clap. Take advantage of your base damage and critical as it will do more damage. Use Primal Split as a last resort when you're about to die. Before the duration ends, leave the Earth Panda to die and WW away the Storm Panda to ensure safety. It's best to make the Earth Panda head straight to the fountain if your enemies can't kill it. Just be sure it dies, and you've escaped the Storm Panda, or you will when you return.", "Triple Threat", "playdota", "http://www.playdota.com/guides/triple-threat.", "Brewmaster", "60");
