      VALUES ("Before we begin, lets take a look at Panda.  Panda has a stat gain of 6.1 per level.  This is slightly below average [average stat gain = 6.2].  His pathetic int gain of 1.25 is going to cause some mana problems, and it may be wise to invest in some nulls, especially when Thunder clap costs 150 mana and when you get your blink dagger, you will have around 400 mana--enough for a clap, blink, clap and nothing else. [although that probably will kill the unfortunate hero ^^]  His Str gain is 2.9--an above average gain, even for a Str hero, and Panda ranks among those with the highest Str gains.", "Pretty much, the success of Panda in this game is based on how well you are able to stay in your lane early game.  Solo bottom sentinel or top scourge is preferable, but its all up to preference.  If you have confidence in your last hit/deny skills, call a solo.<br/>You should leave shop with nothing in your inventory. Although it is possible to wait for the ring of regeneration, you will probably miss the chance to creep block then.<br/> Some regen and the chicken should help you greatly.  Have your chicken bring you components and potions regularly, even if you don't need them at the moment.  Staying stocked with potions helps you to not miss out on any experience.  If done well, and your allies call missing, you should be able to stay in your lane long enough for the blink dagger.", "You should have your Treads and the blink dagger by now, because its time to kill stuff.  The full combo takes 390 mana, so make sure you have enough. Usually Panda has just enough at that phase of the game.  If you find a potential gank victim, approach from behind and give him a thunder clap.  Whack away, and if he runs, stop attacking him, and run alongside until Clap cools down--it shouldn't be too long [Clap cd= 10 seconds].  When clap is ready, blink in front of them, blocking their path, and mash C until clap activates.  Slap them silly until they die.<br/>Most people will just click the dagger, then click an area at the other side of the screen.  Sure, this will work, but the 'Pro' way to blink is called the blink-stop.  This involves blinking directly in front of the running enemy, stopping their movement completely for a precious second.  This ensures that you won't miss your clap and get a few more hits in.<br/>At level 9 you should acquire Primal Split.  This is a very multipurpose skill--it is used mostly for escaping, but with some good micro skills you can use it to attack as well.  Note that the Pandas deal piercing damage, which is halved on heroes.  Piercing damage deals 1/4 to a tower or structure.  However, you won't be able to use Primal Split offensively until later in the game, when you have enough mana to support it.  Earlier, it is better to just blink away.  Later, you can split, then leave the fire and earth pandas to distract/block the enemies, and wind walk the air panda out to safety.", "Late game is phenominal for Panda.  With skadi, his HP jumps to about 3000, and he has enough mana to spam Clap recklessly.  The slow is the most useful feature however, as you can chase heroes better than ever before.<br/>At this point, there is no use trying to face Panda 1v1.  If there is some arrogant troll warlord or something that has the misfortune of thinking he can beat you, then be aggressive.  Use drunken haze to make the enemy miss a GREAT amount of his attacks, stopping permabashers.  The slow from skadi and the 55% attack speed slow from stomp will keep them at bay, and to top it off you get frequent criticals and evade a fourth of all attacks.  If they do try to escape, the skadi frost and blink-stop combo will make sure they die.<br/>Primal Split is very good to use in massive team battles.  In a great battle, you probably wont be able to tell what is going on.  Primal Split breaks up these battles like no other.  You can split, cyclone an important enemy, hurl a boulder at another, and whack away at the weakest enemy.  By breaking up the ranks like this, your team should be able to tear them apart.  If you feel that you might die, use wind walk on the air panda and glide out.", "Bring the Pandamonium", "dotastrategy", "http://www.dotastrategy.com/strategy-3136-BringthePandamonium.html#earlygame", "Brewmaster", "80");
