      VALUES ("With Clockwerk you have to be ready to set up for initiations and ganks. It's all about position so don't place yourself in very obvious positions where people can see you coming. The basic set up is to ult in on an enemy, trap them, then whale away until they die. Pretty simple unless you 1) miss your ult or 2) ult in at a terrible time without backup and it becomes 5v1", "Use Rocket Flare for lane control and for getting those last hits that are out of your melee range. The mana cost is low, so you should be fine spamming it, especially if you have clarities. Keep an eye out for ganking opportunities in other lanes. If you're feeling aggressive and want early kills, try to cog an opponent while they're around your creep wave. ", "Gank. You should carry around TPs and look for good opportunities in other lanes or areas that need support. Pop in, hide behind a few trees, ult at the right time. Catch the enemy unaware and you've got an easy kill if your allies are around. <br/>Use phase boots to move in on an opponent and cog them to keep them from escaping. <br/>Rocket Flare has a map-wide range, so use it to scout or push other lanes. ", "Your ult is best used to force a fight when your team is in a good position and the opponents are not. If both teams are gearing up for battle, you'll most likely die when you jump in, however your team will probably come out ahead if they're ready for it. <br/>Get an Agahnims by this point. It brings your ult cooldown to a really low time.<br/>Again, use Rocket Flare to scout especially if the other team is feeling gank happy.", "Tick tock", "", "", "Clockwerk", "50");
