      VALUES ("Pros: Skills are useful throughout the ENTIRE game, making her a valuable asset to every team during the Early, Middle, and Late stages of the game.Very good harrassing skill. Very good disabling skill. Very good skill with which to takedown buildings (if not the best). Good early mana regeneration, making her hard to lane against due to spammability (if thats a word).<br/>Cons: Even though she has an average stats gain, her base HP is left asking questions, making her weak against spammers.Other than the use of Carrion Swarm, she is very hard to farm with. Nightmarish attack animation makes it difficult to Last Hit and Deny. Horriblific (:D) armor stats.", "Now Krobelus can lane with a lot of heroes and is often used to defend and harras on behalf of Late Game carries so that they get left alone and can farm freely. Heroes like Sven/Phantom Lancer. Once more, Krobelus has a horrid attack animation, but it can be mastered to be used efficiently Last Hit and Deny. By saying Last Hit and Deny, I mean that you should attack the creeps with low HP, the idea is to only use one shot (the last one) to get the creep gold and the minor EXP bonus.<br/>Claim your first tower: Basically when you start aiming towards this, you forget about the Last Hitting and just spam Carrion Swarm to reach your destination; The tower. When the tower is round about at a third of its original health you just activate Exorcism and click attack on the tower. Then you kill oncoming creepwaves with Carrion Swarm", "Krobelus, is perfect for this time in the game. Exorcism, as you have already seen, makes quick work of towers and is fatal in team clashes, and since its only Middle Game few heroes will have the tenQability (Centaur etc) to face your ultimate. Thus leaving Krobelus to move her team upto Late Game with a great advantage as she will lead to succesful pushes. Not only your team will push however, the other team will also be looking to get as deep into your territory as possible, for this you are up there with the best of heroes as to defend a lane against a push and creeps (Also known as Lane Control). Krobelus can be ranked with the top heroes in this category, like the new Keeper Of The Light, due to her Ultimate which can counter a push just as efficiently as it is in making a push succesful, and her Carrion Swarm, as you have seen is also incredible at killing large waves of creeps, and hurting those fragile Intel and Agil heroes. ", "Late Game you are pretty much the same which you have been all game, the team's Pusher, and Defender. Please do note that Defending and Lane Control is not the same, what I mean by Defending is to disrupt enemy team-pushes. During Late Game you are going to Rax ( Destroying Enemy Barracks after third tower, which gives your team stronger creeps ). Maybe you were lucky enough to get a Rax during your Middle Game pushes. Late Game is the moment in which your team will want to make use of the Upperhand they gained during Middle Game, or will like to get back into the Driver's Seat if their Middle Game was not so succesful. Ganking's importance sinks down in this section, and Pushing / Defending's importance is boosted.", "Staple's Guide to Krobelus", "dotastrategy", "http://www.dotastrategy.com/strategy-26196-StaplesGuideToKrobelusDeathProphet.html#earlygame", "Death Prophet", "60");
