      VALUES ("Sorry to disappoint you, but Luci is not a late game carry hero.  His base agi is 11 and the agi gain is 0.9 per level.  None of his skills give him attack speed either.  He is therefore not a late game dps hero and thus you should not build him as such.  Luci's other two attributes are much more impressive.  He has a high str gain and will have over 2500 hp when all is said and done.  His armor is somewhat low but that can be easily remmedied for cheap.  This means that he can function as a pseudo-tank if built right.  He also has 2 powerful nukes.  Also Scorched Earth is an excellent chasing skill.  But all of these skills lose effectiveness as the game wears on.  Therefore the best time for Luci to shine is mid-game and played as a caster/ganker.  He does have a decent int gain, but running around and casting lots of spells can be mana intensive, which is why int and mana regen items are very useful on Luci.  To repeat myself, Luci is primarily a caster/ganker and can function as a pseudo-tank with a few good defensive items.", "As discussed earlier, Doom can solo mid, but that should be left to better rune abusers and early game gankers.  He is much more at home at a side lane, where he can chase a bit if necessary.  This also gives him access to the side shops where he can buy important items like a Magic Stick or a Sobi Mask.  Additionally, enemy melee heroes tend to be on the side lanes rather than ranged heroes, making it easier for you to both farm and harass the enemy.<b/>Devour - You run up to a creep and click devour on it, that's it.  Since Devour has a long cd and relatively low mana cost, it is spammable.  This means that if the spell is off of cool down and you see a creep that you can eat, then eat it.  Try to be devouring something at all times.  This will help you gain both experience and gold faster than your opponents.", "Now that enemies are a higher level than 5 you can start to level up LVL Death so that it deals more damage.  If the enemies are lvl 8 you can consider holding off leveling it to 4 so that you can trigger the bonus damage on your opponents.  Scorched Earth is leveled up since it will increase the potential damage of your combo and will last longer and heal you for more.  Doom is taken when possible because it greatly increases the damage. <br/>Choosing a Target: The most important aspect of ganking is choosing good targets for ganking.  A Clinkz solo farming who can WW is much different that a Sniper solo farming.  Sure Doom can be used to stop Clinkz from using Windwalk, but you won't always have it available to use or be fast enough to cast it before the enemy sees you and reacts.  For these reasons it is much easier to gank heroes that do not have escape mechanisms.  You will also want to consider how much damage your combo can deal and whether or not it will be enough to kill the enemy hero.  A Kunkka has much more hp than a Sniper, so he would be harder to kill and would require more chasing and physical attacks to kill.  A third element is the location where the target hero is.  If they are farming on your side of the map (generally past the river), it is much easier to come from behind or the sides for a gank.  If they are on their side, you can still come from the side but from behind is generally not an option.  If you happen upon them while neutraling, this falls somewhere in between.  On one hand it is just you and the other hero, but you are in a heavily wooded area so there will be lots of trees to use to juke or otherwise escape your chasing.", "Ganking: Ganking in late game is similar to ganking in mid game.  However, your spell combo weakens because the enemy will have more hp and will have had the chance to farm counter items.  In this stage of the game it will be fairly hard to successfully solo gank an enemy hero.  Ganking with an ally is preferred and more effective.  During this stage of the game, enemy carry heroes will be the largest threat to you.  With Doom enemy int heroes still don't stand a chance, and even if you don't have Doom available you have enough hp to tank whatever spell harassment they have.  Enemy tanks will be able to absorb all of your spell damage, but they won't have that large of a damage output so you should be able to withstand that.  Enemy carry heroes are the ones who pose the largest threat to you.  If they survive your initial spell combo they can then out-dps you for a kill.  Be wary of this when you are choosing targets for ganking.<br/>Team Clashes: In the late game period, team clashes will be more prevalent than ganking.  With a second core item that allows you to tank better, your role in the clash is to be up front taking most of the aggro and disables.  The principles outlined in the mid game team clash section still apply and the ideal targets for each type of spell are still the same. ", "Bring Hell To Them", "dotastrategy", "http://www.dotastrategy.com/strategy-34143-BringHellToThem.html", "Doom Bringer", "60");
