      VALUES ("Dragon knight is a Tanker (primary), Semi-Carry, Ganker, and Initiator.", "This is basically my playstyle for DK during early game, though I'm trying to make this as general as possible and not make it everything about me, if you have better and more effective styles then stick with them. We will focus on 2 of DK's primary roles which are the tanker and semi-carry of the team.<br/>Early game DK requires safe play and precise farming.Go to middle lane, remember to block creeps so enemy creeps will end up near your tower for last hitting, it should be not that difficult to last hit with DK's decent starting damage and QB, if your opponent is ranged make sure use the A+attack technique to draw in creeps to stay away from harassment try to last hit and deny but always prioritize last hitting than denying use Breathe Fire at level 5 for mass creep killing. Since we are aiming for quick level 16 leave the rune whoring to your other team mates with bottles or to the disablers who might need regeneration or haste to make their ganks, focus on last hitting/denying every wave and stick with your lane to have as much XP and Gold as possible, make sure to let your team know if someone is missing in your lane in order to avoid deaths on your side, if enemy in lane is missing you can choose either of the following options:<br/>1. Keep farming and Call a Miss <br/>2. Try to gank another lane and get a kill", "This is the fun part of the game where many team fights happen. By this time you are already level 15 or 16, and if you had any luck you already have the core and some of the luxury items. Now, your role in the team is the tanker, therefore you will be the one to initiate the clash. Don't just rush in and die, that's wrong, in every game you need to act smart and be two moves ahead of your opponent. Before the clash starts make sure all of your teammates are in the position to back you up, because mindlessly charging into 5 people is just plain retarded w/o your mates around.Rush in and click BKB and stun the first disabler you see, if you don't see the disabler then stun the squishiest member of the enemy that way your team will devour him by that the disabler will finally show up to support his comrades by then quickly shift your attention to him so he will disable you first. If an enemy is dying and is running away don't blindly chase him too far, you might wanna check if your teammates can do okay if you leave them, if you chase the target too far away and even if you manage to kill him, there's a chance that your team might be wiped out due to your absence, keep in mind that you are a tanker FIRST and a semi-carry second, carries are the ones supposed to be chasing the dying ones and not you. Stick to your team an absorb and give as much damage as possible. Always use your Breathe Fire after stun, this style will give you a good chance to win a clash, just keep cool and think of the next best thing to do.", "This is the hard part, hope that your carry is stacked up since you will have a hard time handling this part of the game considering that the opposite team also has an ace carry in their line-up. Do the same rules of engagement in Mid Game, don't be afraid to die after utilizing all your skills in battle, trust in your teammates to finish the job, hopefully your team will win with the only consequence of you dying, you'd still feel good about yourself knowing that your sacrifice wasn't in vain.", "To Protect and Server", "playdota", "http://www.playdota.com/guides/to-protect-and-serve", "Dragon Knight", "5");
