      VALUES ("Drow was the first hero I ever got good at using. She is a fairly simple hero to use but i decided to write this guide to help newcomers and because not many guides have been updated to include the change to her ulti. Drow is a very good 1v1 hero has the ability to gank almost any hero.", "As drow is a carry/anti-carry you should barely ever be the ward buyer for your team. At lvls 1 and 2 drow is a surprisingly strong hero with silence and a 0 cd orb. At this point you should be harassing most non-double stun lanes really hard. The only hero who's lane control at this point is close is probably huskar (and you don't wanna mess with him for a while). By the time you get to level 3 at the latest you should be harassing the enemy heroes in your lane but keep in mind they are gettin some stronger nukes. If you are up against a dual lane you should focus on just 1 hero this is usually the melee hero if there is one as he will have to come in close to last hit/deny. If there are 2 melee heroes then pick on the one with the least health or the one without an escape mechanism. The only attacking you do should be to last hit, deny or harass. If you are in the hard lane (top sent/bot scourge) and if you are in a dual lane at around level 4/5 and a solo miss gets called be on the defensive. Once you get to around level 6/7 you should think about going back to the fountain and buying some items you should try to farm up 1k gold before you go back but if you can't it doesn't matter. The perfect amount of gold you can get is more than 1700 because with that much you can start getting your core items straight away.", "What you should be doing is farm A LOT without dying and get involved in ganks. You should be getting every last hit in your lane now and also remember to deny creeps when they are on low hp so you don't push too far. If you have pushed too far you will probably notice that some of the heroes have disappeared off the mini map they have probably gone to kill you. If this happens TP out as soon as possible. If there are already heroes after you then try to Silence all the heroes with stuns and TP out.<br/>If there are team fights happening then you should get involved chuck a Silence down to give your team an edge over the other. Make sure you don't run into the action try coming in from behind and throwing down a Silence and Orb Walking their main source of damage.<br/>The main thing is that you are weaker here than in the laning stage and you will be able to dps some heroes, but remember you are still vulnerable to nukes until you get your BKB so don't get too cocky. Its ok to be a little selfish but remember that you are doing it for your team late game.", "This is when drow shines. First when ever you see an enemy hero put Frost Arrows on Auto-Cast this is because by this time in the game you will have such fast attack speed that it is more efficient to have Auto-Cast on rather than Orb Walking.<br/>If you find any lone heroes go around them and HUNT THEM DOWN (that's right i went there). Your teams should be in massive pushes and team fights all the time. Discuss with your team and make sure you focus fire people. You should be focusing the Carry, Disablers, Support, Tanks in that order. Without their carry they won't be doing nearly as much damage. Next you will need to take out at least one of the disablers or their radi carry if they have one. Then their team should fall apart.<br/>Remember if you are focus firing their carry what are they going to do to you??? They will focus you first because you have massive damage now a silence and a slow so it makes sense for them to want to take you out so always be ready to use your BKB/Silence wherever you are or as a last resort run.<br/>Its great to have disablers by your side, but you should at least be able to 2v1 int heroes within the time silence gives. Still as Drow is a fragile hero do not get into the heart of the battle where you will be destroyed by the initiators. The way Drow can destroy other carries in late game is by stopping their game breaking ultis and with her supreme dps output picks off their team 1 by 1.<br/>Play Drow very offensively and be there for the push on every enemy tower. You can rax pretty easily.", "Best Drow guide out there", "playdota", "http://www.playdota.com/guides/best-drow-guide-out-there", "Drow Ranger", "50");
