      VALUES ("Earthshaker is an awesome initiator. For this hero, you want to get the blink dagger as soon as possible, so pick a lane you'll do well in. ", "Kill both creeps and heroes. If you have a double stun lane, you should be getting easy kills. Hide behind some trees, wait until the enemy pushes up too far and fissure. Ideally you want the fissure to cut them off from behind or trap them in somewhere they can't escape. As you're running up to hit them with your tree, your lane partner should be casting their stun. Whoever you're focusing on should be perma-stunned until they die from the combo. ", "You should be focused on ganking now. Grab a couple of your buddies and find someone to gank. Ideally you want this to be more than 1 hero at a time since your ult is so awesome in large groups. Your basic kill tactic is this: <br/>1. Blink in <br/>2. ULT. You must ult first instead of fissure. Why? Ult is basically instantaneous cast time. If you fissure someone might stun you. Then you're stuck in the middle of enemy heroes. <br/>3. Fissure. <br/>4. Stomp for the extra stun. <br/>By this time, your allies should have came in and killed off the opposing team.", "Repeat the mid game ganking section for late game, only now there will be more heroes involved. Make sure you always have enough mana to drop your ult if you're going to blink. If you don't manage to catch most of the opponents in your stun, you'll probably die. Tank up a bit.", "Blinking ES", "", "", "Earthshaker", "1");
