      VALUES ("Oh Earthshaker, what a hero. Although he looks just decent on paper, he is a killing beast if used correctly. Earthshaker is the king of trilanes, and with a blink dagger he can easily acquire a rampage. The way the skill build goes spells out how you should play him, with his best spell : Fissure. <br/> This is going to be the main focus of the Guide, a wrong placed fissure can do almost nothing or even get your teammate killed, and I would easily say that this is one of the hardest heroes to play in a trilane as well (correctly). <br/> So, let's talk about the laning aspect. If you are on sentinel, you will want to go bottom lane, hands down. Scourge, you can either go top or bottom. Now the reason to doing this is a simple fact - the treelines and length of lanes and jungles + unobstructed vision.<br/>Here are the reasons for his starting items, though all of those are listed not of all them need to be acquired.<br/> You are a SUPPORTER, therefore rule of thumb: Wards or courier. Split it with another hero that fills in the same role. (if you do fill in the warding category, REMEMBER - 6 MIN = WARD RENEWAL. A supporter who forgets this will usually get his mid solo killed or lose advantage of a rune, whenever I play pubs, 6 minutes is the mid solo gank time for a reason!)<br/> 3 GG Branches- self explanatory, hence the term GG branches :) <br/> Mana potions- these will ensure you many and many kills if you have well placed fissures, so just think of 50 gold as an investment to protecting your own trilane and gold for a mana boots with the kills you get.<br/>Smoke- with your 1200 Range spell, you can guarantee a successful block without revealing yourself to the enemy.", "Kills, kills, kills. Earthshaker used to be a babysit hero in the turtle era, but in the trilane era he needs the exp advantage. Always sit in the jungle with your partner, and try to set yourself up in the right position so that your fissure blocks a hero in your lane, unless they use 2 tangos on trees, they will have to take the long way around and will usually die very fast. Since your hard carry will just worry about cs, the lane will push itself closer to you giving a better opportunity", "This is where we stand on how good an Earthshaker really is. If you have mana boots and blink dagger, good job. If you don't, then you are SOL for those rampage opportunities, this is where his ultimate shines the most. <br/>With the skill build given, all you want to be doing is the same old fissure block, running around with smoke, OR wait for all enemy heroes and creeps pushing a lane to be grouped up so you can jump on them. as soon as you jump on them, use Echo Slam, Fissure, and totem to finish anybody else off. <br/>Why use ultimate first? It gains more damage based on how many units are in an area. Using any other skill will limit the number of units, so maximizing your ult means using it first.<br/>Veil of discord helps a lot too, reduces their magic armor so you can have an AOE party with your friends. Enough said.<br/>Blink Dagger will be your friend, initation, mobility, ganking, chasing, running away and even dodging stuns if you time it right.<br/>Mana Boots will help you early game, but even if you end up not doing so hot you can spam away at lanes and get some easy gold this way, very useful item.<br/>Bottle? IF for some reason, you have trouble with getting 1000 for mana boots, bottle is your friend. Now usually you want to leave runes for a bottle user, but Earthshaker can use it well with a haste or illusion.", "So, this is when Earthshaker is sometimes a pain in the ass. Your spells don't dish out much damage unless there is a substancial amount of enemy creeps, and the stun could be considered mediocre. You are also jumping into a lot of enemies, so certain death is a likelihood for an ES later on.<br/>Your best bet is having some items, starting teamfights right, or having the map under your control. Buy sentry wards to counter your opponents observer wards, run in a pack while using smoke or let the enemy push and jump on them. You can increase your damage output even further by getting an Aghanim's or Shivas, as well as a heart to incease the damage of totem.<br/>Guinsoo is always a good item for supports, so not much need to be said.", "Blocking Earthshaker", "dota2-builds", "http://www.dota2-builds.com/view-dota2-build.php?hero=Earthshaker&id=241", "Earthshaker", "50");
