      VALUES ("Well to start of my intorduction, huskar is one of my newest favorite hero to use, since all of his skills have great synergy with each other and he has one of the best orb effects in the game with 0 cooldown at level 1, as good as traxex's orb. but IMO is better early game since it has damage over time", "Against: 1 melee hero- This is your best scenario, you have the range advantage and a orb effect skill with 0 cooldown, abuse it!. Harass him as often as you can. If you ever harassed him to half his hp, try to orb walk him to death, if he stays and fight be happy cause you’ll be having your early kill.<br/>1 ranged hero- almost as good as the first scenario, though theyre not that easy to harass because of range, but they will feel each burning spear heavily, since all of the range heroes are frail early except for you, cause you’re the only ranged strength type hero.<br/>2 melee heroes- there is really no problem in this scenario, just use your range and harass them, focus on harassing, denying and last hitting and your gonna get them to a big level gap. Though be aware of melee heroes with nukes.<br/>2 ranged heroes- this would be challenging just deny and last hit as you can, then harass them if possible(if they get to close). Just play safe and you will establish a level advantage over them.<br/>1 ranged and 1 melee hero- as always, last hit and deny, I prefer harassing the melee type and make him use all his tangoes or other healing items.", "Mid-Game is usually the time where most of the heroes are missing and starting to gank, it is also your moment of time to start ganking since you already have your “life break” to initiate your gank, don’t hesitate to ask help from your ally if your not sure in taking out an opponent.<br/>Ganking tip: always aim for heroes which doesn’t have escape mechanism’s or disables. Since they don’t have chances of escaping your combo (i.e. sniper, traxex,tinker). Also aim for heroes with low hp, also gank heroes which are dominating your allies or getting stronger since they will most of the time be the threat in the later stages of the game.", "This is time where most of the heroes (ally or opponent) has there set of desired items<br/>Some of your opponents may not have achieved there core items due to your teams consistent ganks and early domination. Your role at this point of the game is an insane tank, your only best chance of getting kills is from fragile heroes.", "gonz22's Huskar Guide", "dotastrategy", "http://www.dotastrategy.com/strategy-14273-gonz22sHuskarguide.html", "Huskar", "70");
