      VALUES ("Cold Snap – this will be one of your favorite. This is one of the most powerful ganking or focus-firing skill in the game. Besides the ministun effect-which most of the time, disrupts attacking, casting, movement, channeling, etc), it also helps to notify everyone which enemy to attack (especially if you’re the commander). Also used as an emergency skill.<br/>Ghost Walk – your main emergency skill. It is most likely that everyone would use it as an escape mechanism due to its gift of invisibility but there’s a lot more to it. Its slow effect is magical, just follow someone and let someone do something to that someone.<br/> Tornado – this skill is rather amusing. It can be used to scout due to its superior range, It's like an AoE euls for 2.5 seconds only but it has an arival damage which is pretty amazing.<br/>Forge Spirit – spam this. Love this. Always have this.<br/>Alacrity – one of the best support and pushing skill but for me this is the least used.<br/>EMP – a noob killer, and a fantastic lane skill. just cast it in the middle and its either the enemies would flee (so they will be deprived of their experience or any chance on denying or last-hitting) or they would enjoy watching their precious mana disappear. Their call. and whatever decision they make, its your advantage.<br/> Chaos Meteor – your most powerful skill. That’s it<br/>Sun Strike – this skill works wonders, really. My only tip when using this skill, is use it on one target ALONE so that they recieve the full 450 damage.<br/>Ice Wall – one of my favorite skills because it’s huge. Use this properly and you'll surely pwn<br/>Defeaning Blast – your enemies would hate you for this especially during clashes with this, you can tell them “No! Back off! Why aren’t you casting a spell? Don’t attack either”", "Invoke is your priority so get it as soon as you can. Now since its first level starts at level 2, it means that before you learn invoke, you either have one of the three orbs (Quas, Wex and Exort). In every game and every hero, you must consider carefully your first skill and items because roles can be played as early as less than 2 minutes (no creep waves yet). You could be attacking Roshan, clashing on the river, or you can gank or be ganked while level 1 or 2. So make your choice, Quas which creates Cold Snap, Wex which creates EMP, or Exort which creates Sun Strike. For me, I’d prefer Cold Snap because it has low mana cost, low cooldown, and perfect for early ganks. Now, our next priority is to make Exort and Quas level 4 so that we can summon two (2) Forge Spirits. Why? Because it’s better to have company; which is a good addition to your DPS plus it is intimidating so it’s unlikely that you will be ganked when you have two flaming bodyguards on your back. Then after that, while not forgetting to level up your Invoke, you would like to prioritize in maxing out Exort and Wex alternatively. Why Wex? Simply because it adds wheels on your meteor, it reduces the “cost” when you use Ghost Walk (the movespeed reduction), and the best is that you can stop your enemies from attacking for 4 seconds with your Deafening Blast (who wouldn’t want that?).", "This is when Kael is starting to learn and improve more magics. During mid-game, you should prioritize on having your edge on the map and on to your enemies. Gank a lot and push a lot. You’ll need to use most of his skills now but not all every time because your mana isn’t enough unless you have Orchid. Always summon Forge Spirits and spam Alacrity either to yourself or another DPSer like Drow Ranger especially on towers.<br/>First thing to consider is your fragileness and Vanguard solves the problem like a bonus question. Yeah it does because it’s cheap, useful item requirements, and still effective during late game. Next is your mana. Orchid kinda does the job instantly because of its 225% mana regen and its components are cute. (Yeah you should always consider the item components because you need everything anytime everywhere). Next to consider is your usefulness, versatility and potential – AGHANIM’S SCEPTER. With this you can use all your skills in 1 clash. That’s it. Then go for BoT next .", "Oh no! Kael is almost at his most! By this time you should now be feared. You have the items; you should now use ALL of your skills. I require you to smash your keyboard because its clash EVERYWHERE. Non-stop usage of skills, non-stop exort, non-stop fun!", "Azul's Kael", "dotastrategy", "http://www.dotastrategy.com/strategy-35034-AzulsKael.html#earlygame", "Invoker", "20");
