      VALUES ("Able to harass from screens away, Leshrac packs a punch everywhere, pubs or leagues. The ultimate AOE hero that can kill a whole team just by standing in the middle. Taking down towers in a whim, and his pushing abilities are on par with KotL. A killer, A ganker, supporter, pusher, early-late gamer, that is Leshrac. With this guide I shall show you the ways of the Tormented Soul.", "For MY Leshrac, the Middle lane should be your option. why? Because that way, you have access to the 2 rune spawn areas. so you could keep on recharging your bottle. You're also the nearest to the Secret Shop, making the trip to buy a perse shorter. You also have the option to start a gank on bottom or top lanes if you just recharged your bottle, then buy 2 tps, and go back to the Middle lane. But normally go either Bottom or Top, it doesn't matter since you'll be pretty much more of a support in a lane rather than the farmer. Your role is to harass and possibly kill the enemies in the lane with the help of heroes<br/> Farming: Provided you have a below average base attack early on(45-49), your projectile's a bit slower than most(900 missile speed) and a long backswing animation of about 0.8 seconds, animation cancelling to everything Leshrac does is a must. Not only it saves time to chase, it also helps you dodge some megannoying things like Meat Hook and Elune's Arrow.", "Pushing: By the time you have Bloodstone, spamming skills doesn't cost much now. Much more if you have charges(which is most likely by now). <br/>Killing: The problem now is if you're not in a lane. Since we've been killing enemies in the lane via harass->go-4-kill, we would have to leave Pulse Nova on, follow them and wait for Split Earth and Lightning Storm to cool down. Be careful about them sidestepping. Because most people wouldn't run in a straight line, they use maneuvers that may help them escape while your stun is in cooldown.<br/>Clashes: Since mid-game is when carries farm for their lives, and they start defending their base because you guys need to push... and the other way around, Clashes are inevitable. And your role in these Clashes are simple: Use ALL of your skills and GET IN THERE, Stand your ground while attacking, stunning, using lightning bolt, and Pulse Nova-ing, and Retreat when appropriate, Take out those major damage dealers in a clash first like Earthshaker, Enigma, Venomancer, and Tidehunter.", "Thanks to Bloodstone, Kelen's/Guinsoo, no matter how fed you are, carry heroes still outshines you in the game. But you WILL carry your team in clashes. Since you, alone are your team's main firepower in clashes. And that makes you a Support-Carry hero, worthy in both Pubs and leagues. Since you've been pushing like mad, I'd like to point out that After you get your high-tier item, IMMEDIATELY GET BoT . I hope that you guys have Destroyed at least their 2nd tower. And even if you guys are owning, a situation where the tables are turned because their carry was able to farm because of super defending, from what i've seen/played, is highly possible. This is why we would be Keeping the Pressure On Them", "A Walking Volcano", "dotastrategy", "http://www.dotastrategy.com/strategy-20597-AWalkingVolcanoLeshrac.html", "Leshrac", "70");
