      VALUES ("This guide aims towards increasing the overall effectiveness of the player in control of the Lich. Through the exploration of detailed explanation and ideas, this guide will attempt to make the Lich a versatile warrior with a force to be reckoned within battle, as well as filling a support role. With all seriousness aside, the Lich IS my favourite hero of DotA. He is awesome, he is unbelievably effective early to mid game and looks crazily cool. Hope you enjoy reading my guide.", "The Middle lane is recommended for Lich purely because he is a Ranged hero and the opposition usually brings ranged heroes to this lane. However, it may be a good idea to accompany a Close-Combat hero on your side against a ranged foe in a different lane.<br/>With a decently leveled FROST NOVA and possibly with the force of CHAIN FROST, when the opportunity arises, consider taking a trip to TOP or BOT lane to help gank opposition heroes. The slow effect as well as the great damage provided could just be the edge your team needs to make a deadly push towards the Objective. The DARK RITUAL skill provides Lich with an endless supply of MANA throughout the game. Use this to your advantage! Earlier on, Lich suffers from a lack of MANA due to the high costing nature of his spells and sometimes, the MANA cost of Activation Items (Mekansm).<br/>During the course of play, make sure you regularly FROST NOVA your opponents to force them back. Then Replenish your MANA by using DARK RITUAL on a suitable creep. This usually is a full-health creep or one that needs a deny just before the opposition makes the money-making kill. Remember, the more HP the unit has, the more MANA you replenish, and the TANK creeps (Treant or Ghoul) is more recommended than the ranged creep (Druid or Necro).", "During this phase, the Mekansm should have been completed and you should be well on your way into the Sceptre. During this phase of the game, the main idea is to make tower pushes by ganking heroes or taking them out by yourself as much as you can. You shouldn't be lacking MANA as much as earlier on because of the items required to make the Soul Booster.<br/>LICH STRATEGY (CHAIN FROST + FROST NOVA)", "The Lich is not as effective in LATE game as he was in the earlier stages of the game. It is imperative that you make your dominant stand in the earlier games to have a powerful effect on the later stages of the game. During this phase, the Lich's role is to support his allies by providing emergency heals, emergency armour and mass-damage with his CHAIN FROST whenever necessary. Pushing and Defending on-queue and on-time is a definite must as this can alter the result of the game. Do not try to solo enemy heroes as chances are, that they will be stronger than you 1 on 1. Consider telling your teammates then instigating a bait-tactic to create a massacre.", "Sexyrexy02's Litch Guide", "dotastrategy", "http://www.dotastrategy.com/strategy-13384-Sexyrexy02sComprehensiveLichGuide.html", "Lich", "70");
