      VALUES ("N'aix is a killing machine, and my favorite hero, This is my first strategy, and hopefully, with this guide, I'll show you how to destroy everyone and survive possibly with 100% hp left, Some people think this is a weak hero, some think he's strong, I say, its all about the tactics, he's extremely strong, but only if used right, and is probably why some people say he's weak, they cant figure out how to play him right, read this and not only will you be godlike but most enemies wont be able to get away. prepare to be hated by your enemies and making Ursa warriors and Centaurs scream and run at the sight of you.", "Personally I prefer Upper or Lower for two reasons: 1) Got a nearby shop for Death Mask. 2) Only have to watch out from one side not two like when you're at the middle <br/>Hero Killing:<br/> The element of surprise - You can't imagine how important this is, here's a scenario, the enemy hero is pushing and pushing towards your tower, and there most of his creeps die and he stays there for 3secs too long which you use to Open wound him and Rage just as his last creep dies, you and all your creeps attack him, there's a good possibility he will die if he's a Int hero or Agi, but even if he doesn't, you can count on it that his hp will be very low. This tactic works try it, ofcoures you can do it in many ways, from the side, rushing, and ofcoures Infest if you're experienced, can be deadly especially if you get into a Dominated creep they keep close, also, even if you're at 50% hp or so most of the heroes you'll be able to bring down, thats the beauty of it, you pop out of their creep while they are all alone and beat the crap out of them, they wont know what happened till it's too late, its all about the timing. <br/>Timing of skills - Don't be reckless, 15secs if along cooldown when it takes you 5secs to bring someone to 30% hp and making him escape.. don't use rage as the battle begins unless you know you'll need it to survive, in which case you probably wont win cause if you need it at the beginning to survive what will happen after the 4.75secs? ", "Get as much money as possible if you wanna kill heroes, Creep for cash if you want.<br/>Take advantage of opportunities, Look at the map, look around you and judge what's your possibilities, See a hero with low HP? jump him unless he has a friend, you should be strong enough to withstand a tower or afew creeps that shouldnt stop you from kicking his ass.<br/>Don't die, always stay alert, you don't wanna die because you really need items to be able to kill late game, or they will always get away, Rage might be great but when it ends and open wounds does too, you wont be able to do anything without the proper items.<br/>Push on, make them scared of you so you can farm even more money, try to last hit towers and don't be afraid to take some risks.<br/>Buy items as soon as you can, you should be a killing machine by now. <br/>Hero Killing: When you see a hero with 50% hp on the map run straight to them most chances are you can kill them and get away easily. And don't back off unless you HAVE to, the second you stop hitting you stop stealing HP, very problematic, you have no defense from spells unless you got a BKB or a Linken's so careful. USE Infest, it's not useless and is very versatile, example: you're close to one of the enemy's towers, you see him close to yours on the minimap and a wave of his creeps on the way there, why not Infest one of them and pop out ontop of him, most of the times he wont even move 2-3 secs because it'll take him time to realise he's attack, and then its too late, 3secs could differ a Kill from a failed attempt.", "You're almost unbeatable 1on1 IF you chose the right items and play properly.<br/>Don't mind creeps/tower hitting you while you fight another hero.<br/>You can solo towers easily.<br/>Getting money is still important until you get all your gear.<br/>Ambushing is not as important (infest,attacking from behind) BUT still very recommended, especially if they are scared of you.<br/>Timing your skills is always important.<br/>Try avoiding attacking 2 or more heroes without BKB or a Butterfly (depends vs which heroes ofcoures, disablers BKB evasion/high dmg butterfly)<br/>Again if you see a low hp hero, even from far away, run straight to him, nothing to lose + you run fast.<br/>Hero Killing: <br/>Disablers: 1. ALWAYS activate Armlet seconds BEFORE you attack, preferably before you're in range of their disable spell/s. 2. Rage quickly after so they can't disable you, if Disable won't make them kill/escape as the battle starts skip this phase and go 3.Disable is casted and wears off, if they are on low hp use Open wounds, also use Rage ONLY if you know they have another disable or their disable's Cooldown finished, OR if you know you'll need it inorder to finish them off , If they are not low on hp skip this phase go 4. Keep fighting untill you think they are about to run, they will obviously use a Disable or another slowing spell inorder to run, if you know they can do that, instantly use Rage first before they do, and Open wounds second.", "Destroy and Survive", "dotastrategy", "http://www.dotastrategy.com/strategy-14474-DestroyandSurvivewithNaixtheLifestealerbyReaper666.html#earlygame", "Lifestealer", "55");
