      VALUES ("Lina is one of the most powerful nukers in the game, having a spell combo of three active damage nukes(+disable) and therefore tramendous roaming/ganking abilities. She is like a much more aggressive version of Lion. Nowadays, Lina can be commonly seen supporting on 3ple lane or roaming. However, this is not her standart role, because she lacks natural support abilities. I am up to provide you one more option - soloing. This is an option mainly because of her level dependancy and her tremendous power at ganking right after level 6. Also, soloing is the only secure way to have influance on the middle game. ", "Go in lane and choose a primary target by checking your opponents' health, consumables, skills, etc. and attack it. Last hitting is not that important in double lane and your mate will probably need it the most. Concentrate on harassing - 625 attack range and AoE disable are to help you. Never miss an opportunity to place Light Strike Array when you can hit both(or all) your opponents with it. Keep your mana at least at 50%, but don't miss a chance to kill also.<br/>If things in lane go well and your ally can cope by himself, don't lose your time there. Make a camp pull, check the rune, go gank if needed.<br/>If you play smart enough, not to lose all your mana points, Boots should come first. Once having them, you should be able to place Light Strike Array much better - make use of it. The very next item should be bottle if soloing/roaming. If not, just finish your Phase Boots.<br/>When you get to level 6, don't go for the first kill possible. Be patient. You can kill every hero on the map, decide which one will be best. Carries and solo laners have the priority here. After this point, you should never stop roaming.", "Here is your peak. You got all your nukes now and it's time to start killing intensely. Map awareness is the key. Always watch your position and keep an eye on the minimap. Go for every rune. Use terrain advantage on your side - as an example, when beinig chased a highground + Light Strike Array can save your life. Note that Light Strike Array also destroys trees - this should prevent your opponent from continuous juking.<br/>When ganking don't rush Light Strike Array if your opponent is not near enough. Wait for your ally or wait him go wrong. Once you have your Eul's/Dagger this will no longer be a problem.<br/>Eul's has the priority, because it provides the much more needed: Int, Mana regen, MS, Disable. These are a dream team for the middle game of every nuker. It is Ok to delay Dagger because of this, but don't delay it too much. If for any reason things don't go well, just go for another item - Janggo, Ghost Scepter or just some Bracers will help you survive.", "Although a heavy nuker, you are far from powerless even in Late game. All the strategies of Middle game are still viable here. Because of Fiery, now you are capable of combining both physical and magical damage in battle. This is to help you against magic immunity and high HP pools, which are both common in Late game. You still have two disables, so all you have to do is to position yourself and wait for your time.<br/>Even if you get caught, having Eul's, Dagger, Ghost Scepter and Hex, your opponent will surely lose a lot of time (trying) to kill you. Notice that all these items are good both for attacking and protective purposes. You are not an easy one to take down.<br/>All you have to do in order to finish the game is win a decisive team battle. Gem is something to help you do this - you have no more important items now, use your gold to buy one if needed. Even by your own, you are pretty good at pushing(2 AoE nukes, 60%IAS).", "Master the fire", "playdota", "http://www.playdota.com/guides/master-the-fire", "Lina", "50");
