      VALUES ("Lina is sort of like Lion in some way, except that she has more nukes. I have played her a lot recently and found out that whenever a face Pugna or Anti-Mage its actually pretty challenging. She has a good ganking potential but is very weak without mana or disabled. She is sometimes underused and underestimated but thats not true. In the right hands, she can be a great hero killer.", "Once you get your starting items choose a lane. The best lane for Lina is mid because it's easier to hit people in mid lane using Dragon Slave than other lanes since mid lane is very short. I suggest instead of automatically attacking get last hits, after all, Lina's damage isn't that good. Don't harass until level 4 or 5 because your spells does low damage early on. If you harass someone enough you can draw kill once you get your ultimate! Just farm well in general.<br/>Once you reach level 6 you hit the spotlight. Most heroes probably have paper hp or really bad spell resistance. When you get your ultimate, try to kill someone! It's better to team up with an ally and gank but you can perfectly handle this yourself: Find a weak hero, Make sure your ultimate is not on cooldown, Cast Light Strike Array first to make sure he/she dosen't fight back, Cast Dragon Slave array on him, Use ultimate on him/her", "Now that you're in mid game, you get even more spotlight! You should've probably farmed up your core right now, if not then use Light Strike Array and Dragon Slave to farm. Once you get your ultimate to level 2 start ganking. Again, heroes are paper right now so take advantage of your ability to kill! I would suggest getting your mid game items ASAP since that will make you a even better nuker. However, watch out for anti-spellcasters and disablers, it's probably better to team up with a teammate first or else you could get killed. ", "You kind of loose the spotlight in late game. This is when most heroes gets stronger and you'll find that you sometimes can't kill a hero just by yourself. So I would suggest that you always stick to an ally. Your ally can get a hero down to low hp while you nuke him/her. Since your stun isn't really that good in late game, get Guinsoo as a disable. Lina isn't that good in late game overall. But she is still very deadly and can pwn you!", "Mistress of Nukes", "playdota", "http://www.playdota.com/guides/mistress-of-nukes", "Lina", "55");
