      VALUES ("Banehollow to most people isn’t that strong but nonetheless he is not that weak either. That is why Banehollow is not that popular in pub games and online games. Well, as what I have observed anyway. IMO, Banehollow is one of those heroes that can adapt into different situations when needed. Built to be a hero killer, pusher, carry, tanker and into other types. I propose a different outlook for Banehollow, moreover, with this strategy I hope with optimism that Banehollow would be viewed differently.", "Preferably go for the bottom lane if you’re in the sentinel side and top lane if you’re in the scourge’s side and go solo. Because these are the lanes closer to your tower which is advantageous for melee heroes to avoid getting harassed while last hitting and denying creeps at the same time. And if your assigned into a different lane make sure you block the creeps so that you could still tower hug. If you’re assigned with another teammate then better if it’s a disabling, slowing or stunning hero so kills would come easy for later on. Follow the basics stated above and you will be able to farm for exp and gold easier. Stay patient when going up against nukers and harassers use your wolves in farming instead and leech at the sides for exp and remember to move constantly to avoid being a easy target (do not activate level 1 wolves!). At level 3 summon wolves is where you start to harass and keep them from getting the gold and exp. This is where creep pulling and blocking helps greatly, because the farther your enemy hero from their tower the longer the distance of the wolves to chase him down and keep them from farming. Remember not to auto attack and just last hit the creeps (refer to basics) use your wolves as scouts to scare away enemy heroes.<br/>At this stage survivability, leveling, and farming is your prime importance. So stay as serene as you can and avoid being killed. As much as possible destroy the first tower in your lane as fast as you can. At level 5 you can destroy the first tower in your lane. I’ve done this many times before and this is very easy actually. The trick here is to always pull their creeps but at the same time kill them fast", "This stage is where you become known and should start to get the kills. At this part is where fear begins to creep in to the minds of those with fragile hearts as soon as they see you in your wolf form. He can kill a full HP hero just by chasing them down while biting their arses! You heard me right, but even those with disabling skills, stunning skills or slowing skills. But if you sense that you are still too weak to go up against the enemy heroes then you should continue to farm in your lane and neutral creeps. Remember that hunting for heroes all the time and failing at killing delays you from getting experience and gold. So when your ulti is still cooling down remember to keep farming. At this juncture heroes starts to establish their ganks and move across the river unto your side in groups to look for kills. So be careful, always look out for missing heroes and when farming for neutral creeps use your wolves as sentries to avoid feeding to the enemy (refer to skills of your skills)<br/>Farm, farm, farm! Always assess the situation before doing something too aggressive. If you get ganked do not hesitate to use your wolf form to get away from sticky situations. Team up with your allies in getting effective kills. You’re a chaser! But do not get carried away in chasing down farther to the enemy territory alone for it may be you who would get ganked in return.", "Here is when you amend from being a Hero Killer to a Pusher. Why? Ultimately the purpose of pushing is to destroy the towers and eventually finish the game. Would you rather be beyond godlike and lose? or killing spree and win? Well, I like being beyond godlike and winning at the same time like the next guy does! But anyway, late game is when team clashes would happen more often since they would want to kill as many heroes as possible to be able to push further without interruptions which would be your team’s goal as well. Remember to activate your howl constantly which costs few mana as it contributes a lot in your efforts in pushing. Don’t push just to destroy a tower and get killed a long the way. NO! NO! This is not worth it at all because respawn time takes too long at this stage and most likely the enemy can kill creeps so fast that your tower would be destroyed faster that you did theirs.<br/>However don’t forget that you are still a Hero killer so most likely you’d still be able to pawn a couple of heroes and push at the same time. Don’t forget about your wolves they may not do much damage to enemy heroes at this point but the permabash is still good. I’ll explain more further.", "Banehollow: A hero in more ways than one", "dotastrategy", "http://www.dotastrategy.com/strategy-15342-BishsGuideBanehollowaheroinmorewaysthanone.html", "Lycanthrope", "60");
