      VALUES ("If you are looking for a hero killer right off the bat, you have come to the right place. I'll show you how 'deadly' can Night Stalker be.", "FIRST OF ALL, WHEN PLAYING NIGHT STALKER, YOU MUST ABSOLUTELY SOLO!!!!! THIS IS VERY VERY IMPORTANT TO SUPER GOD-LIKE HERO KILLING!     GO TOP IF YOU STARTED TOP, GO BOT IF YOU STARTED AT BOT!<br/>Earn at least 500+ gold before the first night. Be at least level 6 before the first night (idealy level 8). Do not let yourself be the victum of 'first blood'. The above is our goal for the very early game playing. When facing more than 1 ranged heros as enemies, try to stay back. If that is the case, facing two ranged heros, gaining experience will be your top priority. If it's possible, however, getting the last hit of the enemy creep(s) will help you build your eoconomic status at early game playing. But only do this when you are 100% sure that you will not be hit more than 3 times by your enemy and enemy heros. Staying behind will pretty much earn gold to around 500 when first night arrives. ", "Check your mini map and know who is missing!<br/>Check your mini map and know who is missing!<br/>Make sure the lane you've selected do not has the missing hero(s) around!<br/>Engage that unlucky player.<br/>Start your killing with your level 4 Void attack. This work best when you walk out of surprise for your enemy. Then after he is slowed from you Void, just start wacking him until he's dead. Usually there will not be any hero that can out run your, however if cases that you feel you don't enough time to wack him physically to death before he escapes, you may use another Void. I know saying this sound stupid, but do watch your mana pool since you want to OWN.", "Well, this is late game, so just make these item in any order you feel you should/need: Heart, Daedalus, Satanic. Or Divine Rapier vs Radiance and Daedalus (your pick). Heart for defense or satanic for aggressive. ", "Deadly Night Stalker", "dotastrategy", "http: