      VALUES ("This guide is going to be about a hero that can turn things into frogs, sheep, etc, throw a net and hold someone for almost 5 seconds, make orange lightning appear out of his hands, and summon a gang of evil serpents. Oh, and he can shoot lasers out of his glowing eyes.", "Any lane is fine. When you lane, you want to be dominant over your opponent. Usually, you shouldn’t be so focused on last hitting, but more on denying, and harassing. If you get Ether Shock, you can use that to last hit occasionally but make sure you hit the enemy, too. You do this by making sure the enemy is near the creep wave and target the creep closest to him/her. The Ether Shock should hit the target creep, the hero, and some other creeps.<br/>Ganking involves you cooperating with your teammates to kill a hero. Usually you pop out from the jungle when ganking. Shackles is your most important skill when ganking. Make sure you notify your teammates when you want to gank someone.", "In mid game, you should have at least 1 or 2 levels of voodoo already. With voodoo, you can do the Shift Queue Combo: First you Shackle someone, Next you hold shift while using voodoo on the shackled hero. This combo allows you to voodoo a hero right after shackles ends. This is good because it helps prevent blinkers from blinking away or stunners from stunning.<br/>The Ward Trap involves you trapping a hero in your serpent wards. Of course, just targeting a hero with your wards will never work because the enemy heroes will move. That is why Eul’s Scepter of Divinity helps you trap someone easily.", "Late Game is when pushing counts the most. With your Wards, you can push a tower down with ease. In late game, continue using Shift Queue and Ward Traps and teamwork, Teamwork, TEAMWORK. Teamwork is the most important thing with Rhasta. He was born a disabler and he should be used like one.", "Summon Serpents and Shoot Lasers", "dotastrategy", "http://www.dotastrategy.com/strategy-32048-TheHeroThatCanSummonSerpentsandShootlasersoutofhiseyes.html#earlygame", "Shadow Shaman", "70");
