      VALUES ("Silencer is a strong hero for League and pubs alike. He's not noob friendly I can guarantee you that, using silencer will require fast fingers and above average map awareness. Silencer is a hero that doesn't have much room for creativity so you won't be seeing something unique here. Take note this is a BATTLE SILENCER.", "First start off with 2 tangooes and 2 circlets and head out to the mid lane(sacrifice a circlet if your the one assigned to buy the chicken for the team.). Silencer must solo he needs the extra experience and gold to be effective mid to late game. When in your lane you should last hit, deny, and farm like your life depended on it. Be aggressive, and harass often with Glaives. It's called 'orb-walk' (see the orb walking section for a more detailed explanation) you press 'W' and left click the enemy hero to cast a single glaive on him in order to harass him. You might wonder, 'What's the point of this it does so little damage anyway', The damage will add up if you repeatedly harass the hero like this. The reason why Glaives is such a powerful harassing too is because creeps will not attack you if you harass a hero by manual casting it. Normally if you attempt to attack a hero the creeps will focus their attention on you but if Glaives was manual casted, it is counted as a spell therefore it will not trigger creep aggression. Early game is all about lane control for Silencer, I suggest you rush Dagon at this point to make the most out of it. If your dominating in lane control turn your circlets into Nulls but if your having a hard time I suggest you turn them into Bracers. Once you hit Level 7 your Glaives have a 0 cooldown, abuse it by Orb-walking like no tomorrow.", "Your Mid game performance greatly depends on your early game. If you completed your dagon then I suggest making the most out of it by Kill stealing as often as you can. That's right! I want you to Kill Steal, unlike all the other heroes silencer benefits alot more from getting a kill since every kill will give him 1 more int. If you are completely against kill stealing your Dagon still has another purpose to fulfill. Although Orb walking helps you kill running heroes, you can't expect to orb walk every hero to death, Dagon is used as a finisher in case if they survive your orb walk. By now I suggest you start farming for an Eul's, It helps alot in getting him out of sticky situations since silencer doesn't have a natural escape mechanism. Remember you should still be orb-walking when ever you engage an enemy hero don't neglect it.", "There are 2 possible outcomes once you hit late game. If you have been doing poorly early - mid, your going to be food. However if yo had been scoring alot of early to mid game kills, you'll be a late game monster. Work on your Guinsoo since your Eul's charges would problably be used up by now. Here you should use global silence for the team either to stop a channeling spell or to give your team a free 5 second BKB. Keep your glaives Auto-casted now since you have plenty of mana to spare, in team clashes your role is the DPS hero, your unreduced damage glaives can rip apart high armored AGI heroes and your last word can prevent them from using chain nukes. By now it's ok to sell the Dagon in order for you to buy survivability items such as a Heart. If the game Drags on get a hyperstone since it's the best way to boost your DPS.", "Nortrom the Glaive Thrower", "dotastrategy", "http://www.dotastrategy.com/strategy-4726-NortromTheGlaivethrower.html", "Silencer", "60");
