      VALUES ("Being one of the baddest tanks in the game - between your Strength, your lifesteal, and your Rez - your position on your team is logically to be the tank. You provide good support to your allies with Hellfire Blast and Vampiric Aura.<br/>However, doing so is somewhat boring and this leads to the impression that Leoric himself is boring, which is not totally true. In this guide, the goal is to become a killing machine. Don't forsake your allies, but you aim to go kill things, not just support your team. Which is why you concentrate more on hero-killing items than tank items. You can still be the team tank, but you can also have a lot of fun.<br/>My sole philosophy regarding tanking is this: if you become too big, then the other side simply won't attack you and instead concentrate on your weaker team-mates - and when this happens, you have let your side down. This is why this guide almost totally omits pure tanking items: the objective is to get them to focus on you - but if you have to do it by killing everything you can, all the better for you.", "Radiant: Top Lane, Dire: Bottom Lane. If you are getting the Ring of Health to start, you have to be there (at one of the side ones) when the creeps spawn in order to afford it, so that denotes going Top or Bot (good, because going Mid is suicidal for Leoric anyway). However, if you're near the main Secret Shop in addition to a side one, you can also finish your Perseverance early without losing major experience, and stay in your lane a while longer.<br/>Leoric harasses by using the one thing he has in abundance: pure striking power. Only applicable if you can out-harass your enemies, such as one range, one melee, or two melees. Not applicable against two range, unless they are being stupid. If you are in the aforementioned lane situations, just steer clear of them and level for a while; if you have a ranged allied lane-mate, have him cover you.<br/>Do not spam Hellfire Blast! I can not stress this enough, do not use this unless you really have to. Your mana constraints at this point are extremely low.", "At this stage of the game, Leoric can walk into any but the Ancient creep camps, kill all of the creeps, and walk out again with full hitpoints and mana - since you have good regeneration, lifesteal, and don't need mana to creep. So farming is obviously very easy. If you want to farm in a lane, just be careful about enemies - have good map awareness and don't get ganked. If a single enemy comes... the chances are you can fight them, but thats in another section.<br/>Pushing: You are very tanky, so you can be the shield for your allies and/or creeps - make sure the tower attacks you instead of them, this is essential for both groups: shield your allies so they aren't damaged (you can deal with damage better than they can), and shield the creeps so they don't die and continue dealing damage to the tower.<br/>Killing heroes: Leoric is a simple hero when it comes to killing, since he can only do two things: use Hellfire Blast and attack.<br/>Ganking: Try to surprise them by coming out of the trees or fog, or from behind them. Use Hellfire Blast on the target immediately, cancel the silly 'I'm gonna stand here watching the fire thingy' animation and attack them as soon as the stun is launched. If they fight back rather than running, so much the better for you, because you have better lifesteal than they do (unless they got Satanic this early somehow, yea right). Keep attacking them until they flee, then just run behind them until Hellfire cools down and use that again. Rinse and repeat! The target will eventually die, provided you have decent mana regeneration.", "Battle Furies! When you get more than one of these, the splash damage increases. No diminishing returns or any of that annoying stuff, but pure addition. 35% each, so if you get three you do more damage to the enemies you aren't directly attacking. You run in, stun someone, attack them, watch their allies come to help... then you get a crit and do the helpers a ridiculous amount of damage from your multiple Furies, because theres nothing they can do about it besides not come that close (which means that you chew on their now-abandoned ally and then come for the others), or disable you a whole lot (for which you have bought a BKB I hope).<br/>", "Leoric Versus the World", "dotastrategy", "http://www.dotastrategy.com/strategy-10919-LeoricVersustheWorldbyShimrra3.html#earlygame", "Skeleton King", "65");
