      VALUES (" In most cases, I'd say he functions as a ganker/semi-carry. He can also be a pseudo-initiator with your sprint and blink dagger if you choose to get it. Crush is what allows him to initiate and gank and basically functions as your bread and butter throughout the game. It's also one of the best stuns in the game, lasting 2.5 seconds at all levels in an aoe around you. Already looking pretty good but it also boasts a ridiculous 8 second cooldown. This means that you can easily get multiple stuns off in a teamfight.", "Unless you have a melee hard carry on your team, you should ideally be going safe lane (top for dire, bot for radiant) with a ranged support, but you can go long lane too. Your sprint should let you escape most ganks if you see them coming early. Starting items generally include a shield, tangoes/salve, and hatchet to help you lasthit. Hatchet can easily be substituted for stat items like ironwood branches if you are confident in your lasthitting. Slardar needs farm to be effective, and ideally you would have priority over lasthits in your lane. Your first item should be ring of health, then boots of speed, then vanguard. You should finish your vanguard by 10 minutes. Even if you’re doing terribly on last-hitting, 10-12 minutes shouldn’t be too hard to aim for.", "So now you’ve gotten Vanguard and hopefully finished your treads. What next? Depends on the enemy composition, really. At this point you should get either blink dagger, more survivability, or more killing potential. BKB is essential in a large portion of the games you will play, as any team worth their salt will have at least some amount of CC so consider getting this next. As a bonus, activating BKB makes Slardar’s model really fucking huge, which is hilarious. However, if you don’t see it being necessary, consider getting blink dagger or a damage item next.<br/>Blink dagger is pretty situational, and I only really get it if our team doesn’t have a real initiator, but it’s a pretty solid item on Slardar all the same. You can easily catch people by surprise by blinking and crushing as opposed to sprinting towards them with 15% increased damage taken and giving them time to spread out. If you are looking for a damage item, Desolator is the way to go. Not only does it give you a bunch of damage, but it decreases armor, which stacks with your ult.", "One thing that I haven’t mentioned yet is Slardar’s ult. After you hit level 6, you should be casting this on everyone you see. It basically works as a mini double damage for your team on a single target and gives you true sight for a long time. How cool is that? It also has an absurdly low cooldown and low mana cost so this should be the first thing you cast on enemies before ganks/teamfights. Note that this also gives your crush more effective damage as it is physical and your amplify damage lowers armor. Even cooler. You should prioritize invis heroes to make them cry bitch tears.<br/>Teamfights are relatively straightforward; you basically just blink/sprint into battle with BKB on try to crush as many people as you can while casting your ult on cooldown and rightclicking shit. Basically you want to be in the middle of the fight and cause chaos while your carry rapes the enemy team. You have huge teamfight presence, so take advantage of that.", "It's a Crushmas Miracle", "dota2-builds", "http://www.dota2-builds.com/view-dota2-build.php?hero=Sladar&id=396", "Slardar", "60");
