      VALUES ("Mercurial is able to Desolate opponents for pure damage if she catches them alone, and Disperses damage intake, reflecting it in the area around her. She can hurl a Spectral Dagger at opponents, which will slow and damage enemies, as well as allow Spectre to pass through material objects and travel across any terrain. She should be feared as a constant presence, being able to Haunt images of herself upon all enemy heroes from any distance, and even reform her actual self into any one of those images to physically enter a fight. -Playdota.com", "Always get a lane partner, preferably a good babysitter. You'll be a big target, so you'll need a buddy to help. There isn't any other way to farm except through last hitting, actually. I don't advise using dagger as a farming tool this early in the game especially since it's high mana cost and high cooldown might kill you later when you need it and can't access it. Since this is earlygame, it is highly unadvised to try to harrass an enemy with your high manacost dagger. Although, there will be cases where you'll have no choice. To harrass and farm at the same time, do what the earlier video showed, but making sure to aim at the hero and at the same time the dagger would pass through creeps. That way, the creeps are damaged/killed, and the enemy hero has been harrassed. Now, when your laned with the heroes i have informed you of early, the annoying enemies, try to call for ganks whenever possible. You can't farm while dead, nor can you farm when one step away from your tower will cost you your life, yet those precious creeps full of gold and exp are right there. You want them gone, even if it's just for a bit of time.", "Midgame = Ganking phase, but don't forget to balance out farming. Yes, i know you can use Haunt to gank the other side of the map but do you want to do that when you see all your enemies failing to push top? You're freefarming bottom lane. Keep the gold coming! Haunt will be our primary hunting and clash skill. Those images do insane damage to jungling heroes especially because your images get the Desolate skill and your mana burn (if you have that diffusal already). Neat huh? Come to think of it, with diffusal, your images to a whopping 65 pure damage alone! Haunt will be used to hunt for missing heroes on the map. They would either be jungling, soloing rosh, killing rosh altogether, or preparing for a gank. You wouldn't want to miss those stuff right? You'll be bound to find an ursa who is soloing rosh with this skill at least once. Trust me. Once you use haunt, you'll always see giant dots on the map, regardless of where they are. If you're going to gank with an ally, pick the one that is somewhat alone and somewhat close to your ally, if they aren't simply close to your ally and alone. If you have your diffusal however, you can gank heroes soloing your jungles, trying to take down rosh, loners who farm too far from their towers. Some Spectre users tend to just rush in beside a hero who is alone. Please don't. Make sure it's safe to engage. Don't panic, they'll be there for a whole 3-4 seconds so you can replace your image.", "Lategame is generally when Spectre totally pwns. Our midgame pwnage is only somewhat of a 'prequel' to the real deal. In this part of the game we have those crazy chaotic clashes (remember, we aim for that) and mad pushes and defenses. ALWAYS, always, bring a disabler with you lategame. It's just really important since you wouldn't want to get raped by bait. So now clashes are coming in left and right. As a carry with Haunt, what do you do? If you're IN the fight, initiate with it. Enemy initiators are always somewhere hiding getting ready to blink in, so cancel that initiation and let your ally tide get in there! If you're in another lane, and the enemy initiator isn't seen while the rest of his allies are, again, haunt to initiate. reality beside the initiator (unless it's ES) and kill him while your team rapes his initiatorless team. If however the initiator is with the pack (which will be very unlikely), wait for him to ulti. He's in the middle, meaning if you use your ulti and your team goes to ambush, your illusions will get raped, rendering you technically useless in the fight. So, if Magnus is in the middle, wait for him to ulti, THEN rape with Haunt.", "Being alone has never been this scary", "dotastrategy", "http://www.dotastrategy.com/strategy-34074-BeingalonehasneverbeenthisscarySpectretheemokiller.html#earlygame", "Spectre", "65");
