      VALUES ("Take note that this guide doesn't show you on how to play Barathrum the professional way, this guide just shows some knowledge on how I play Barathrum personally. Barathrum is one of my favorite heroes since he can easily kill a lone hero easily, which makes him one of the best hero picks in DOTA. ", "Early Game your not as effective as you look right now since we need items for you to kill any enemy easily. Remember, you're a late gamer so you're effective in late game. Buy your items and pick a lane. Pick only top or bottom lane, don't pick the middle lane and leave it for your teammates to handle. If the lane is hard because of heavy lane controllers, better call for a lane switch or gank and make them pay late game. Last hit creeps as much as possible. Last hitting creeps will make your lane mate think you're greedy so it's better to share some creeps for your lane mate because this will affect your teamwork. Share some creeps as possible, don't get greedy. This is a bit serious because some people are telling that they're not going to help you if you don't give him/her some creeps to eat. When you reach level 4, level 5 or level 6, your teammates will expect a gank so participate in early ganks as much as possible with your Charge of Darkness and try not to get reckless with it. ", "This is where you shine. Once you have an MoM and some core items then you can kill any lone heroes without breaking a sweat. NOTE: DON'T CHARGE HEROES WHO HAS A DISABLE OR MORE BECAUSE THEY CAN DISABLE YOU WHILE YOU'RE CHARGING HIM/HER WHICH MAKES YOUR LONE GANK NAERLY USELESS. Bring someone with you to ensure an easy kill while ganking a disabler. <br/>This is important: If your ganking a lone hero alone, look at the map first if your target is separated from their allies and you see their allies in different separate places in the map. And when the target IS alone, charge him/her. Oh yeah, if there are no enemy heroes in the map besides your target, charge that target if you can BUT EXERCISE MORE CAUTION WHEN DOING THAT because a clever enemy team will try to lure you out by letting someone squishy from their team come out of the map. Once your fooled and you fell into their gank, you're dead. Your life is precious so DON'T DIE IF POSSIBLE and bring a TP and teleport home after you successfully ganked and killed a target alone. Again, if you don't want to die when your lone gank goes wrong, bring a TP or someone with you to ensure a kill like what I've said before. <br/>ALWAYS CHARGE WHEN YOUR TEAMMATES CALL FOR A GANK", "If you have completed your Luxury Items before the game ends, no one can stop you. Like what I've said before, when clashes occur, better let someone from your team initiate first then go for the Charge. Finish the game ASAP before the enemy team can get their Luxury Items. Finish the game within 60 minutes. ", "Mother Earth Guide Me", "playdota", "http://www.playdota.com/guides/mother-earth-guide-me", "Spirit Breaker", "70");
