      VALUES ("Barathrum, rarely seem on the competitive scene, is a powerful chaser who dominate most of mid game. He has the abilities when coupled with items can make him permanently hasted. But unlike the Involker and Krobelus who can't / shouldn't be used as a chaser (they rely on their spells to kill), Barathrum can fully utilize the speed by converting it into damage.", "Farm for your past. Farm for your present. Farm for your future. Just farm. Take Charge if you are facing a weak lane. With a stunner, you can grab First Blood. Don't die. Leak exp if you need to level up, but don't take harassment. You will get them back later, so don't worry. If you die, you will screw up your mid game performance.", "It's time to shine, you should start ganking by the time you hit level 6 till level 16. Didn't you want to get back on those pesky nukers? Now is your time to hit back. Save the ultimate for the escapee if you can. Kill the first one fast (using MoM, Armlet or anything you have), let your mates jump one the other one, and then finish him off too using your ulti. If there are a carry present, give him the second kill. You need gold yourself, and you wouldn't be farming much. You will be passing the rune spot lots of time as you are ganking, so take Bottle if no one have a need to rune whore. It will solve your mana problem. A quick Aghanim can be useful, only when you get bottle or Cyclone with it. Otherwise it will only cause you headaches (worrying about your mana)", "I once heard a wise man said: A lone hero is a dead hero, even the bulkiest one. Stick to your team. Pick the target before the team battle start and stick to your target. The priority will be the one with spells that can change the tide of the battle but not the carry. He will (and should be) stronger than you this late. When you finished off your target, get back and help the others asap. Get as many luxury as you can, but save money for buy back. You can dish out quite a lot of damage as you are the second DPSer.", "Pubbers guide to cownage", "playdota", "http://www.playdota.com/guides/pubbers-guide-to-cownage", "Spirit Breaker", "75");
