      VALUES ("The old raijin thunderkeg has been praised by a lot of players and used by a lot to win their matches...But when the new raijin came, he was hated by a lot of people...which is sad. But people only started to see his potential when he was used by pros in the tournaments...So now, I will try to help you in using raijin thunderkeg in your matches..From a late game DPS carry now truned into a ganking, spamming, late game chasing carry, I present you...my guide to RAIJIN THUNDERKEG (and hopefully my first and successful guide ^_^)", "If you encounter a:<br/>1v1 melee - greatest thing for you...you can spam your remnant freely and hit him with your overload-ed attack...be cautious though...you're fragile and he might have a nuke or  skill or whatever that can hurt you...<br/>1v2 melee - be careful...watch out for chain stuns or nukes...and deny and last hit too...attack him when given a chance...<br/>1v1 ranged - if you're close enough, use remnant then attack with overload...deny and last hit creeps...watch out if they have nukes or stuns<br/>1v2 ranged - be careful...deny and last hit too...ask help from allies if they spam spells on you...", "In midgame, here is the time where massive pushes occur with a lot of clashes and ganks around the map...This is also the time where things get COLORFUL for you: Calling the shots for pushes because remnants and overload kills creeps easily, Going by yourself or with an ally and looking for farming enemies, Farming enough creeps to gain as much gold as possible for your items", "If the game haven't finished yet, Then this is the time that you really shine!!! Enemies can't kill you, You are wtfpwngazooring everyone around (except your allies) and You are now destroying their Ancient...There's nothing much left to say now because it's almost impossible to lose if your carry or you is beefed up already (You are the carry remember?? ^_^)", "Unknown's guide to Raijin Thunderkeg", "dotastrategy", "http://www.dotastrategy.com/strategy-26238-BZZZZZTTUnkn0wnsguidetoRaijinThunderkeg.html", "Storm Spirit", "40");
