      VALUES ("Your priority is to max out Storm Hammer as soon as possible. This is one of the best stun in the entire game. You should also get some stats and War cry along the way. The stats will be useful for you because you need mana in order to land your stun frequently. War Cry, on the other hand, is a really useful skill to avoid been gank and also to push. The bonus armor is pretty decent and the movement speed will get you out of bad situations. You should also max out your ultimate at the normal levels.  When you did all that, go for Great Cleave. It will give you a free Battlefury and it will be pretty strong for your farming. The reason why you should not pick Great Cleave early is because of your base damage. In the early game your cleave will be totally useless and will push lane for no reason.", "In the early stages of the game you should lane in a side lane with a support hero. Get as many last hit as you can so it you will be able to move around sooner. Pick a Ring of Basilius and boots of speed as soon as possible. The bonus armor from basilius will be really helpful and the mana regen given by this item will let you spam Storm Hammer more. One thing that you should note here is that you should try to get some kill in the early game in your lane because it will allow you to be more usefull at long terms. If you can't get enough farm nor kills, you should start to roam because the enemy team will outfarm you quickly. So in that case you should switch to a more support role. However if you kill a lot of heroes, getting an urn is a good idea because it will give you nice mana regen and heal.", "In the mid stages of the game you should now have an Armlet,Treads and a Drum. With those items you will be able to contribute a lot in team fights. Your treads will let you attack faster and give you some good stats while your Armlet, in combinason with your ultimate will destroy the enemy. The drum will be usefull to give you extra speed. If your farm is really good you should pick a blink dagger instead. That will be more usefull in team fights because you will be able to position yourself at close range so you will be able to stun the crap out of everyone and auto attacking them. At this moment you should start to be pretty decent. Try to initiate the team fights with your blink and dont be afraid to go in because you are a Rogue Knight bitch! You will be freakin tanky and you will deal massive damage. If you are good with Armlet, you should start trollin the enemy team with it. Also you should use your ultimate in every team fights. Man you are turning Red, that's badass... Oh and it give you a lot of damage.", "At this point you will want to get some luxury items. But be careful. Those items depend on how the game is going. If your team is going to push a lot you should upgrade your basilius into a Vlad. It will be usefull for your team to push a lot. In that case you should also consider a pipe and an Assault Cuirass who will be helpful for pushing and team fights. If you are more in team fights you should get a BKB. It will give you some nice stats but also magic immunity. Espacially if the enemy team have a lot of stuns and disables. At this point the game should be over. If not, save money for buyback.", "Attack of the Sven", "dota2-builds", "http://www.dota2-builds.com/view-dota2-build.php?hero=Sven&id=375", "Sven", "70");
