      VALUES ("In my opinion, Tidehunter is the most NOOB friendly heroes in the game. He's naturally tanky from his abilities and stats, plus he's one of the best examples of an ITEM-INDEPENDENT hero in the game. Also being a support/tank, you won't usually be getting focused down in fights, and also your own team won't be AS pissed at you when you screw up, since you're not the carry and all. WINS ALL AROUND!!!<br/>Tide is a really simple hero. His main roles are to Disrupt and Tank. If you have more kills than deaths, than you are probably taking too many kills from your carries.<br/>To put it simply, your job is to set up your carry for kills and make them look all pro while you take your silent victory in the backround. it's a humble life.", "My usual opening items are MAGIC STICK, 3 BRANCHES, and 2 TANGO. This is assuming im against a lane that will be using abilities fairly frequently to give me charges on my magic stick. If this isn't the case, by all means, pick up a HEALING SALVE. These items will give you plenty lane sustain to last into mid game. If you are the main support on your team, do not forget to pick up a couple WARDS and for the love of God, BUY A COURIER!!!! As stated before, Tide is a very item-independent hero, so it's not like you need the money anyways. Be helpful. Please.", "This is where we want to get those ARCANE BOOTS and BLINK DAGGER. Now i choose arcane boots over the other boots because you get utility. you get enough mana to spam your abilities and you get to give mana to your lane partner. i find those things WAY more valuable than Treads or Phase boots. But once you have enough mana regen, and are sittin on piles of money, feel free to swap these out for some Boots of Travel.<br/>BLINK DAGGER, in my opinion, is the most essential item for any tide to have. i can't imagine playing a successful game without one. you get that movement, and that blink-ult combo right into the middle of the opposing team. it allows for better chasing and escaping (an area where tide isnt exactly the greatest at). overall, this item is ESSENTIAL, and if you don't agree, well i don't want to play with you. so there. hmph. ", "This is where the situational/luxary items come in. now is the time to build tanky since your opponents now will usually do enough damage to actually worry you. my go to item is SHIVAS since it gives me everything i need. armor, mana, and that sexy aoe slow. From there you can build whatever your team needs. it's up to your own play style!! ", "Dat Tanky/Support Tide", "dota2-builds", "http://www.dota2-builds.com/view-dota2-build.php?id=370", "Tidehunter", "50");
