      VALUES ("Tidehunter is a great initiator that might actually survive battles due to his high tankyness. His Anchor smash also gives him DPS. Easy hero to start playing, however it takes a little practice getting his ult right and being able to initiate at the right moments for teamfights. ", "You can easily get a kill early game if you're laning with a disabler, but don't get too comfortable in your lane and don't just stay there farming. You don't need too many items to be successful, so it is better to use your time to cut away the farm of the opponents carries or go gank other lanes.", "Get the blink dagger as soon as possible. Once team battles start coming around, your team is going to need you to initiate with a blink ult. If placed correctly, Ravage can easily stun the entire opposing team. If you're new to blinking: DON'T COME FROM AN OBVIOUS AREA. If the enemy sees you running up to them they're going to spread and ruin your chances of catching them. They're pushing a tower? Hide behind some trees off to the side. Blink in when they're in tower range, Ravage. Slap them with your fish. Gush as they try to run away. Phase and catch up. Slap them with the fish again. ", "Tank up in order to avoid dying at every battle. You'll be initiating and tanking so you need to soak up as much damage as possible to allow your team members to survive. <br/>Get wards. Your team will need them for ganks and map control.  ", "Tideeeehunter", "", "", "Tidehunter", "60");
