      VALUES ("Do you want a hero that can play almost all roles? Do you want a hero that can bring 5 heros down to low HP all of its own? What a bout a hero that can take down creep waves less than 2 seconds all the time? Not to mention can TP anywhere at anytime it wants. What about a hero that almost always has the most kills while also having the most assists and less deaths? There's only one hero for you. Yes, Boush The Tinker. I see outdated guides to Tinker here in dotastrategy.com. And many people in public games don't play Tinker do its max potential. I'd like to add that the Tinker guides here, build Tinker incredibly weak, with the skill builds maxing March of Machines? With that said, I will help and show you guys how to build Tinker to its maximum potential.", "Tinker's lane control is one the of the most powerful out of all heros in DotA. Tinker can bring down his opponents almost always half hp all the time in his lane. He is very powerful early gamer, and should be played aggresively to take this early game advantage. Level up your Laser, and move on to your lane. Best lane is mid solo. Spam your laser. Even at level 1. It deals the exact amout of dmg it says on the tooltip 80/160/240/320. Spamming this will keep your opponent to play defensively, and cripple them from farming cos of the the % miss. You can spam this alot, since Tinker's starting mana pool is pretty high. Laser's casting range is 550, which is as far as your attack range but a little bit closer. So when using Laser, immediately attack your opponent straight after u laser while your still in your attack range. Do that by animation cancelling. Doing this will deal as much dmg as possible in ur lane.", "You now have Boots of Travel. Breathe a big sigh of relief. Even if the rest of the game goes badly for you, Boots of Travel alone means you will always be able to be helpful to your team no matter what happens. Ganking: This is your first priority. Being able to teleport anywhere around the map, you should keep a look out for an opportunity to gank heros. Especially heroes that are low in HP. You look for allies that can help you achieve a successful gank. Ask them to initiate the gank (slow or stun) when your TPing, then finish them off with your combo. When the gank is successful, and the battle is over, rearm and TP back to base. When you want to gank a low HP hero that think they are safely farming in a lane, TP to a creep where that enemy cannot see you. Then finish them off with your combo. Make use of your Rocket's range. Rocket's range is 2500. Which is very very LONG (about  2 screens). If you see an enemy that is extremely low in HP, don't hesitate to TP somewhere far away. As long as you still have sight of that low HP hero, use Rocket and grab that easy kill.", "ALWAYS BEING AIMED FIRST IN TEAM BATTLES: Go last in the battles. If they know that you are the biggest threat in the game then they will often focus you first (Which often happens to me when I play Tinker). So let the enemy focus your allies first by standing at the back of the group, and then moving into the battles last. Then while the enemy is aiming one of your allies, there's your chance to go in and help him out.<br/>COMBAT AGAINST MASS STUNS & DISABLES: Same method as above. Let your tank heros soak up the disables. When all stuns and disables have been used, thats your time to move in and do the damage. If they have too MANY stuns and disables, go for survivability items such as Linkens. BKB is an option if these stuns are really a big issue. (BKB cannot be rearmed).<br/>AGGRESSIVE PUSHER ENEMIES: When your enemy love to push all the time, keep repeating your defending method which is the MotM+Rocket combo. Since aggressive pushers always have massive creep waves with them, MotM will give you a ton of gold from that. Then when you have enough gold, go for a Shivas Guard for more AOE DMG. Then you can start outpushing your enemies by using Double-Shiva farm. Aim for Manta if you need to push towers.", "The Perfect Hero", "dotastrategy", "http://www.dotastrategy.com/strategy-31184-ThePerfectHeroBoushTinker.html", "Tinker", "50");
