      VALUES ("Combo: The Ava&Toss Combo is not really as hard as you might think. You just have to use both spells (Avalanche and Toss) as fast as possible on the same Target. Why is it so good? Because a tossed enemy gets hit by Avalanche twice!<br/>Uphill Suprise: Sometimes when you wait on a hill you will get lucky and find an enemy, who can't see you because you are in fog. So you can easily land the Combo on him.<br/>Free Blink Dagger: When you have Heroes like Axe or Slardar in your team you can toss them into the fight first and Dagger right after them, so they don't need a Dagger to initiate with their stuns.<br/>Runes: Whenever you get a Haste or Invisbility Rune you have to get a kill, if you don't get at least one kill you did something wrong.<br/>Backdoor: It's not a strategy for losers. You are just showing how insanely strong you are when you destroy their whole base alone... while backdoor regeneration is active.", "Buy a Stout Shield to reduce the amount of damage the enemy can do while you farm. You could also get a Ring of Protection instead, but I prefer the Stout Shield. Some cheap stats are always good and of course healing items are a must. After some farm you should buy a bottle so you can cast your spells more often. I would also suggest to go Solo Mid or Solo Bot, because you need as much experience as possible so you can kill enemies sooner.", "Arcane Boots are very good to stay on lane and to gank around the map. With the mana you will never have to go back to the base (for mana). Blink Dagger is a must on Tiny. A Tiny without dagger is a weak tiny and doesn't use the full potential of the hero. With an early Dagger you can Insta-kill almost every Agility or Intelligence hero in the game. But wait. Your skills scale late game, but they still cap at some point, so the next best item is Aghanims Scepter. It gives you enourmous damage with the cleave and range. It also makes Tiny one of the fastest Tower pushers in the game. Sadly Tiny has very low Attack Speed due his low agility and his ultimate. That's why you have to buy a Mask of Madness. It gives the most attack speed for the gold which makes it the best item after you get Aghanims.", "Attack speed, and more attack speed. Tha's what Tiny truely needs. That's why Mjolnir and Assault Cuirass are extremely good items. Mjolnir gives a lot of Attack Speed, almost as much as Mask of Madness, and it also gives you a nice mini AoE nuke in fights which adds to your cleave you get from Aghanims. Assasult Curiass on the other Hand gives you good Armor, but its also the only benefit yout get by finishing your Hyperstone. So basically Butterfly is much better for your defense than Cuirass and it also gives 5 attack speed more, damage and evasion. I would go for pure Life items like Heart or Bloodstone because you already have a lot of life due to your high STR gain, and other items benefit you more. For example a Black King Bar can win you the game. You can destroy one tower and two barracks when you activate your Black King Bar (unless your enemy deals insane physical damage). Deadalus is also pretty neat on Tiny because of his Cleave and the lifesteal, but you will hit very slow when you dont have other items like Butterfly, AC or Mjolnir first.", "GentlemanDota presents Tiny", "dota2-builds", "http://www.dota2-builds.com/view-dota2-build.php?hero=Tiny&id=337", "Tiny", "90");
