      VALUES ("This is a guide to the Ursa Warrior, Ulfsaar. This little bear can cause a whole crapload of damage when the right items are acquired. Even only with a good HP item and a good source of movespeed, this mammal can be unstoppable.", "Take the bottom lane if you are in the Sentinel. Take the top lane if you are in the Scourge. Right after picking the Ursa Warrior, say 'I am bot' if you are in the Sentinel or 'I am top' if you are in the Scourge.<br/>ALWAYS go with an ally in a lane. Always. ALWAYS! NEVER TAKE THE SOLO LANE! NEVER! You ask: WHY?!?!?! Then I say: Because you are an mid-late gamer, your enemies would want to annihilate you early on so you won't OMFGPWN them at mid game. If you do decide to take the solo lane, please, for the love of DotA, please be careful. Deny at your own risk. Last hit at your own risk. Keep farming and farming. Farming and farming. Hell, grow some corn for all I care. Tomatoes too. Grow whatever a bear eats. Bamboo or something. By the time early game ends, which is usually about 10-12 minutes in game, or even earlier. But when Vlads and Boots are acquired, the early game for the Ursa Warrior is over.", "In this phase of the game, the Ursa Warrior usually ganks a lot with other roamers, like ES or VS. You can even take on the gigantic golem, Roshan. Before you kill Roshan, cast Overpower and Enrage. Attack 12 seconds after you casted both spells. By doing this, you don't have to wait for the cooldown WHILE fighting Roshan. Cast both spells. Note that the small icons for the spells are blinking, indicating they are about to expire. When this happens, start killing Roshan. Also, take a look at my items. I took STR Power Treads to help me with HP and Enrage. Remember, tell your allies you are going to Solo Roshan. Ask them to watch out and keep guard near Roshan's Area, since your enemies will suspect something. You are the Ursa Warrior, they'll think if you're gone that you are automatically massacring Roshan. True most of the time. Keep farming some more. Gank some more. Gank gank. Gang kill. Gank. If you don't feel like you want to gank some enemy heroes, farm. Farm like there's no tomorrow. After getting a Phase Boots or a Strength Power Treads, whichever one you choose to get, the next step is a decent HP item: Vanguard", "What the hell? The game dragged on? WHAT THE HELL???? It's fine. Just make sure that you don't die. Make sure your team wins. If the game manages to drag on this late, there is one item left to get: Heart of Terrasque", "Go Deep", "playdota", "http://www.playdota.com/guides/go-deep", "Ursa", "40");
