      VALUES ("Ursa Warrior: his name describes his idiosyncrasies. A warrior born of Ursidae blood, he seeks only to kill and to rid the world of his enemies. Ursa Warrior is definately one of the best hero killer in DotA. All of his skills synergizes with each other perfectly, and his attribute gain beyond compliments his playing style. This guide will be based on Ursa's favorite hobbies: kill, gank and destroy. I hope you enjoy reading this guide, and that you will learn to rack up your kills by 'Unleashing the Rage'.", "1. Stay Alive. 2. Farm. 3. Get First Blood if possible. It is important not to get harrassed too much early because Ursa is very fragile in this stage of the game. Lane picking is very important because it will determine who's serving up first blood and who's drinking it. You should always avoid going against ranged harrassers and nukers. The golden rule is to 'pick on someone your own size', and I say this not in the tough-guy tone of voice but in the 'please don't hurt me' attitude. So go against heroes that are melee. Also, farming should be easy if you've picked a good lane opponent. Last hit and harrass at the same time with Earthshock, and get a few cheap shots whenever possible.", "Mid Game is where the fun begins! With Enrage and level 4 Overpower, you should be able to kill almost any hero one vs. one. Your main priority during this stage is to farm and kill heroes that get in your way. It is best to pick a side lane and farm by yourself when you are not involved in anything else. If you come across any weak intelligence or agility hero, kill them. Until you get your Yasha and BKB, your main priority is to farm. It is important that you do exceptional during this stage of the game because it will determine the fate of your late game. If you rack up lots of kills during mid game, you will be a monster in late game once you have a HoT and Butterfly.", "Late Game Priority: <br/>1. Win the Game (This should be your main priority every stage of the game)<br/>2. Kill (Ursa can only get stronger as time passes)<br/> 3. Push (Push for the win!)<br/>If you have been successful with your ganks, continue. If your ganks aren't going so well, there are 2 options:<br/>1. Turn into a tank. Rush into battle and absorb all the damage. Die for your team if you have to.<br/>2. Continue your ganking. A bad mid game doesn't always mean a bad late game. You can still get plenty of kills in the late game even if you haven't been doing so well. Follow the mid game ganking guide.", "Unleash the rage", "dotastrategy", "http://www.dotastrategy.com/strategy-22158-UnleashtheRageAGuidebyDaMan2000.html", "Ursa", "30");
