      VALUES ("Hello and welcome to my guide about Lesale Deathbringer, the Venomancer. I am going to try to explain how powerful this hero can be and give advices on how to play him.", "Well, this will change depending on your type of play and the way you decided to build Veno. But in general you should either harass and deny like mad or roam and gank like a boss. Poison Sting lets you keep opponents at low HP while Venomous Gale lets you slow them so someone else can handle them(that doesn't mean you should just drop the Gale and leave). Once you get your Poison Nova teamfights are starting to get sick. REALLY SICK. That ultimate is fucking great, abuse it. Use the wards to guarantee yours and your ally's safety.", "You have your Poison Nova, you have your Gale ... what are you waiting for? Kill, gank or push depending on your build ... or just do it all! Who said you can't gank mid, then swing top for a kill and push a tower? Towers are gold advantage for your team and gold is an important factor for the outcome of the game.", "Bad luck, you are not as good as you were earlier. Well, you still got the goddamn OMGWTFBBQ ultimate, right? Just make sure you get it off in the best moment and don't waste it on crap and you will be kinda fine. At this part of the game you shouldn't wander around all on your own. Go with a teammate, preferably one you can help out.", "Make them Crawl", "playdota", "http://www.playdota.com/guides/make-them-crawl#value7", "Venomancer", "60");
