      VALUES ("Almost all Weaver players think, that Anub'seran is a late game carry. This is riddiculous. My guide will show Weaver as a early and mid game, item independent monster, 'cause in this time Weaver shines the most. In return of his killing capabilities, great escape and pushing mechanism, our bug is very fragile, has a poor stat gain(except agi) and is quite mana dependant. This also shows that he's not a newbie-friendly hero. In the wrong hands Weaver will just feed the opposite team instead of raping them.", "First thing: don't die. Seriously. Weaver can't afford to die, cause you need at least lvl 1 Swarm. Try to creep block. If your partner can't pull - you should do it. Don't expect to get many last hits, because Weaver attack animation sucks. When you hit lvl 3 try to kill. Hide in woods, pick some Int or Agi hero with low hp pool. Cast Swarm and go with Shukuicki. After this you should attack. In many situation you will grab a kill, because Swarm is a perfect dps skill in early game. Either you will kill him, or Swarm will. Don't try this if you're against 2 disablers (like Lion + Sven) cause if they have little brain in their skulls, they will kill you very easy. Remember - you're a nightmare for fragile heroes like Zeus, Mortred or Traxex.<br/>Don't stay on your lane too long. Get Treads or Phase Boots and after achieving lvl 6 go help your team. Scenario is always the same: suprise Swarm, Shukuichi, attack (remember to have Geminate on cd) and chase with Shukuichi.", "Game is getting harder for you. You need some items to be useful. Still your presence is very usefull however hard-carrys are getting powered up with their items so you're not the biggest baddass in team anymore. Shukuichi slowly looses it's effectivness as a harassment tool. You should get some hp. Still try to take down low hp heroes if you see them farming, but be careful not to die.<br/>There will be a lot of pushing and defending now. Remeber you can stop creep waves with Swarm which makes you exellent pusher. Geminate attack is your main damage source now, so Crystalys/Buriza would be a good choice. Your ulti costs 0 mana now so mana burners can suck your balls. Remember to stick with your team. Being alone is very dangerous to you at this stage.", "Game is practically already ending (if it haven't finished yet). Push, defend, stick with your team. If you haven't got Buriza yet - now it's the time.", "Invisible bug who travels in time", "playdota", "http://www.playdota.com/guides/invisible-bug-who-travels-in-time", "Weaver", "50");
