      VALUES ("Start out with 1x Tango, 1x Clarity and 1x Healing Salve (this potion is extremely important if you're going to solo lane or mid).<br/>The gloves are just to have better survivability and eventually upgrade them into a bracer or two.<br/>The branch gives an extra bit of stats instead of having a Tango/Clarity more, which I prefer.", "Once you're last hitting and getting gold, I'd suggest getting your boots next followed by a bottle. The bottle is great for recovering HP/MP and staying longer in lane without having to return in base. Along with the fact that quite a lot of runes are useful to Zeus and that when you bottle them, you get an additional 3 charges. This provides a long sustainability for Zeus to stay on the map and help out with ganks.<br/>When returning to base, consider making your gloves into bracers if you have the spare gold.", "Once you have a bottle, bracer and your boots, your next move should be to upgrade those boots to Arcane boots since Zeus has some problems with his mana, especially when harassing and/or doing his burst damage.<br/>After this, you should definitely start working on his Aghanim Scepter, starting off with the Staff of Intelligence.", "Personally, I feel Zeus still has a strong late game. After you have your Aghanim Scpeter, it becomes extremely annoying for the opposing team to be low, as they always have to be on their guard and you can assist ANYWHERE on the map. The Refresher Orb allows you to have INSANE burst at the cost of your mana bar, but it is extremely worth it. Once you have the Refresher Orb, start working on other situational items.", "Zapping with Zeus", "dotafire", "http://www.dotafire.com/dota-2/guide/zapping-with-zeus-god-of-olympus-546", "Zeus", "70");
