      VALUES ("Zeus is an intelligence hero who's primary role throughout the game is to provide high amounts of magical burst damage.<br/>As a hero who lacks health and is very reliant on positioning through the game, Zeus tends to be a difficult hero for beginners to play. Despite that, after reading this guide you should be able to understand the hero better and play him proficiently after your first few games a result.<br/>As fore-word to the guide, Zeus, as a hero, is what you would consider a glass cannon. High amounts of damage, able from long range, yet breaks easily upon contact. Because of this, we have to make up for it by positioning ourselves the best we can during fights to avoid focus.", "The majority of the time you play Zeus, it will be as a solo hero in the middle lane. With fast levels, an early bottle and some rune-luck, you should be able to go around and get some kills, gaining map dominance for your team.<br/>The starting build I gave for Zeus: 3 tangos 3 clarities and 3 branches allows for Zeus to get his fast bottle so that he can go around and get those early runes. You should be last hitting with arc lightning and using the clarities to get the last hits, and hopefully have your bottle up for the 2 minute rune. With a rune like an invisiblity or haste, if the opportunity should arise, you may be able to gank the other lanes. If there isn't an opportunity, simply stay mid and try to farm up your arcane boots while attempting to get the rune every two minutes.", "By level 7 you should hopefully have your arcane boots in addition to your bottle, and magic stick. At level 7, as zeus, you are an extremely exceptional hero-killer. With all your spells, arc lightning, lightning bolt and your ultimate, you have over near 600 damage in instant burst potential. You always want to be carrying a TP scroll ready to counter-gank for your allies and the carry on your team.<br/>The next item you want to be picking up would be a force staff. This item is simply an exceptional item on zeus because Zeus is entirely reliant on positioning for survival and staying as far as possible from heroes and staying safe. Force will allow you to play more aggressively in fights because you'll have an escape mechanism if you get caught in a sticky situation.<br/>As Zeus, you want to make sure that you are at every gank and team fight possible, and also be on edge ready to counter gank when they're ganking. Trying to predict when they're ganking and setting up a bait is also a very good choice of action.<br/>Fighting with Zeus throughout the game doesn't vary much based on items. The biggest change to team-fighting will occur when you get your force staff, which will allow you to play more aggressively because of the escape mechanism it provides.<br/>Zeus excels in the early-mid game, so while he does scale into the late game well, he's stronger earlier and as such you should be looking to end the game earlier in general.", "The ULTIMATE key to Zeus is POSITIONING above all else. If you nail that into your brain, you can become a master of Zeus. I have dedicated an entire section of this guide to blast into your head that positioning is the most important part while playing Zeus.<br/>Stay on the outskirts of the teamfights, casting spells at maximum range unless chasing.<br/>Look at the mini-map every time you ultimate to see where the enemy heroes are positioned, and to ensure that you aren't getting flanked from behind<br/>Be ready<br/>Make sure you aren't going to be hit by large AoE ultimates such as tidehunter, void, sandking, earthshaker etc. If you're hit by them, then you are going to become an easy prey for the enemy. You are to stay FAR in the back, away from those.<br/>Use fog, trees and terrain to your advantage whenever possible. Even if they chase you into the terrain, you will be very difficult to kill and you may have delayed them enough for your team-mates to come save you.", "The God of Thunder", "dotahut", "http://www.dotahut.com/guides.php?g=41#chap5", "Zeus", "75");
